        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 11 at 4:13PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 413 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles north of Vaughn, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pastura and Pintada.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
